<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b> Japanese is listed as one of the official languages of <a href="/wiki/Angaur" title="Angaur">Angaur</a> state, <a href="/wiki/Palau" title="Palau">Palau</a> (<a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/show_country.asp?name=PW" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Ethnologe</a>, <a href="https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/ps.html" class="external text" rel="nofollow">CIA World Factbook</a>). This official status is disputed; there were very few Japanese speakers on Angaur as of the <a href="http://www.spc.int/prism/country/pw/stats/PalauStats/Publication/2005CENSUS.pdf" class="external text" rel="nofollow">2005 census</a>.</li>
